  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (bounded applicability, clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Operating envelope explicitly bounded: flow rate 2–6 L/min, rotational speed 2000–4000 RPM, hematocrit 35–45%, fluid temperature 35–37 °C. Validation activities densely cover this envelope at 15 operating points. Applicability constraint limits use to adult CPB with blood viscosity 2.5–4.0 mPa·s and pump inlet pressure −50 to +20 mmHg.",
